Document: FontVariation
Path: godot/classes/class_fontvariation.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of a FontVariation resource in Godot Engine, including base font, offsets, OpenType features, palette customization, and variation settings.

Property: base_font
Type: Font
Description: Base font used to create a variation. If not set, default Theme font is used.
Setter: set_base_font(value: Font)
Getter: get_base_font() -> Font

Property: baseline_offset
Type: float
Description: Extra baseline offset (as a fraction of font height).
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_baseline_offset(value: float)
Getter: get_baseline_offset() -> float

Property: opentype_features
Type: Dictionary
Description: A set of OpenType feature tags.
Default: {}
Setter: set_opentype_features(value: Dictionary)
Getter: get_opentype_features() -> Dictionary

Property: palette_custom_colors
Type: PackedColorArray
Description: An array of colors to override predefined palette. Use Color(0, 0, 0, 0) to keep predefined palette color at specific position.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.
Default: PackedColorArray()
Setter: set_palette_custom_colors(value: PackedColorArray)
Getter: get_palette_custom_colors() -> PackedColorArray

Property: palette_index
Type: int
Description: A palette index.
Default: 0
Setter: set_palette_index(value: int)
Getter: get_palette_index() -> int

Property: spacing_bottom
Type: int
Description: Extra spacing at the bottom of the line in pixels.
Default: 0
Setter: set_spacing(spacing: SpacingType, value: int)
Getter: get_spacing() -> int

Property: spacing_glyph
Type: int
Description: Extra spacing between graphical glyphs.
Default: 0
Setter: set_spacing(spacing: SpacingType, value: int)
Getter: get_spacing() -> int

Property: spacing_space
Type: int
Description: Extra width of the space glyphs.
Default: 0
Setter: set_spacing(spacing: SpacingType, value: int)
Getter: get_spacing() -> int

Property: spacing_top
Type: int
Description: Extra spacing at the top of the line in pixels.
Default: 0
Setter: set_spacing(spacing: SpacingType, value: int)
Getter: get_spacing() -> int

Property: variation_embolden
Type: float
Description: If not equal to zero, emboldens the font outlines. Negative values reduce the outline thickness.
Note: Emboldened fonts might have self-intersecting outlines, which will prevent MSDF fonts and TextMesh from working correctly.
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_variation_embolden(value: float)
Getter: get_variation_embolden() -> float

Property: variation_face_index
Type: int
Description: Active face index in the TrueType / OpenType collection file.
Default: 0
Setter: set_variation_face_index(value: int)
Getter: get_variation_face_index() -> int

Property: variation_opentype
Type: Dictionary
Description: Font OpenType variation coordinates.
Note: This Dictionary uses OpenType tags as keys. Variation axes can be identified both by tags (int, e.g. 0x77678674) and names (String, e.g. 'wght'). Some axes might be accessible by multiple names. For example, 'wght' refers to the same axis as 'weight'. Tags on the other hand are unique. To convert between names and tags, use TextServer.name_to_tag() and TextServer.tag_to_name().
Note: To get available variation axes of a font, use Font.get_supported_variation_list().
Default: {}
Setter: set_variation_opentype(value: Dictionary)
Getter: get_variation_opentype() -> Dictionary

Property: variation_transform
Type: Transform2D
Description: 2D transform, applied to the font outlines, can be used for slanting, flipping and rotating glyphs. For example, to simulate italic typeface by slanting, apply the following transform Transform2D(1.0, slant, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0).
Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)
Setter: set_variation_transform(value: Transform2D)
Getter: get_variation_transform() -> Transform2D
---CHUNK---
Document: FontVariation
Path: godot/classes/class_fontvariation.rst
Summary: Sets the spacing for a FontVariation to a specific value.

Method: set_spacing(spacing: SpacingType, value: int) → void
Sets the spacing for the given SpacingType to the specified integer value in pixels. This value is not relative to the font size.